name: Pantai Banjar
address: RX88+X89, Jl. Segara, Banjar, Kec. Banjar, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81152, Indonesia
review 1: **Pantai Banjar**, located in Buleleng, Bali, is a serene black sand beach renowned for its natural hot springs. Nestled along Bali's northern coast, it offers a tranquil escape. The beach is lined with palm trees, offering stunning views of the Bali Sea. The main attraction is the natural hot springs, known for their healing properties. Visitors can soak in the warm, mineral-rich waters, believed to be beneficial for skin and joint ailments. Basic facilities such as parking, toilets, and local eateries are available. Pantai Banjar is perfect for swimming and sunbathing, offering a peaceful retreat away from the crowds.

name: Villa ibiza bali
address: Jalan Melati, Banjar, Dencarik, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81152, Indonesia
review 1:
Hello, in itself a beautiful villa but...
Unfortunately it needed a bit of maintenance at the time. Roof leaking, mold on the walls.
The villa is only conditionally suitable for a baby, next to the villa is a river / stream the access is not secured, when it has rained, this washes garbage to the coast.
Unfortunately we 1.5 year old baby and an adult got sick in the villa. (Campylobacter, Norovirus and EPEC) The exact reason is not clear, food, water quality... the remaining days in Bali were of course anything but relaxing.
It was our second visit to Bali and we have traveled a lot around the world, but nothing like this has happened to us before.
review 2: Be aware this house is very remote. The house staff is excellent but they cannot fix the fact that you are hours away from anything. If that is what you want then this place is exactly what you need. For our group though, it proved to be a bit too far away for our group.
review 3: Fantastic villa with stunning views and friendly staff. It has everything you could wish for as a holiday home.
review 4: Wonderful and quite place to stay

name: Villa The Mango Trees Bali
address: RX89+XWP, Dencarik, Banjar, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81152, Indonesia
review 1: The villa is absolutely amazing. Its design reflects an exquisite taste that seamlessly blends tradition and modernity. Every corner has been thoughtfully appointed with all the necessities that one could possibly need, showing a deep consideration for guests' comfort. The staff is another remarkable aspect of this villa. Their professionalism is exceptional and they consistently go the extra mile to ensure your stay is truly unforgettable. Their kindness and attentiveness is genuinely heartwarming. A stay at this villa is definitely a delightful experience.
review 2: We had an awesome time here with our family. Beautiful villa, great staff. Loved going fishing on the boat at the villa with the captain and the staff cooking our catch for dinner. Great lication, very relaxing.
review 3: The villa itself is very beautiful and the staff is excellent. The beach in front of the villa is dirty and there is quite a lot of thrash in the water.
review 4: Well maintained, comfortable villa in the quiet location outside of Lovina

name: Villa Akasa Segara
address: Unnamed Road, Dencarik, Kec. Banjar, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81152, Indonesia
review 1: We stayed almost two weeks in the Villa Akasa Segara in the north of Bali and enjoyed our stay a lot. The staff were amazing, super friendly and they made us feel welcome at all time. Especially I want to name Iluh, our property-manager/housekeeper, she is the best chef, super kind and funny, knows a lot about Bali and did everything to make everyday special to us. We'd defenatly spend our next holiday here again. Thank you so much
review 2: Amaizng! Great staff, wonderfull view, very clean.
review 3: Amazing amazing amazing! Wonderful people. Iluh made our stay even better with her excellent cooking.
review 4: Absolutely excellent staff, pool and garden. But you should not expect something great from the location and the beach.
